00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:05.730
Acme is a extensible ADL developed at Carnegie Melon University and

00:00:05.730 --> 00:00:09.960
University of Southern of California's ISI. It was specifically designed to

00:00:09.960 --> 00:00:15.111
facilitate the interchange of architectural descriptions among tools. And

00:00:15.111 --> 00:00:18.884
it comes with a variety of tools of its own. Including Acme Studio,

00:00:18.884 --> 00:00:24.230
which is a graphical editor by which you can draw architectural diagrams.

00:00:24.230 --> 00:00:29.444
AcmeLib which is an API in languages such as Java and C++ for

00:00:29.444 --> 00:00:32.819
interacting with these artifacts. And

00:00:32.819 --> 00:00:37.330
AcmeWeb which is a document generator. More information about Acme can be

00:00:37.330 --> 00:00:40.869
obtained by following the link on the class' resource page.

